    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And David distributed them,.... The posterities of Eleazar and Ithamar into certain classes or courses: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "both Zadok of the sons of Eleazar, and Ahimelech of the sons of Ithamar; these were the two principal men of the respective families, the one was high priest, and the other \"sagan\" or deputy; or they both officiated as high priests alternately, until the one was removed in Solomon's time, and the other established alone. And now their brethren the priests, who were under each of these, are the persons David divided into classes: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "according to their offices in their service: to perform their office as priests in the service of the temple in their turns. ",
        "children": [
